\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Unified framework for evaluating document chunking strategies across retrieval paradigms. Documents from BEIR and GutenQA datasets are segmented using one of several methods. Depending on the configuration, embeddings are generated either before chunking (\textit  {pre-embedding chunking}) or after full-document encoding (\textit  {contextualized chunking}, e.g., Late Chunking). Resulting chunk embeddings are indexed and evaluated under two retrieval settings: (1) \textit  {in-document retrieval} (needle-in-a-haystack) and (2) \textit  {in-corpus retrieval} (multi-document). The pipeline supports multiple embedding and generative model families, enabling controlled comparison across chunking paradigms and model capacities.}}{3}{figure.caption.2}\protected@file@percent }
\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
\newlabel{fig:chunking-embedding-pipeline}{{1}{3}{Unified framework for evaluating document chunking strategies across retrieval paradigms. Documents from BEIR and GutenQA datasets are segmented using one of several methods. Depending on the configuration, embeddings are generated either before chunking (\textit {pre-embedding chunking}) or after full-document encoding (\textit {contextualized chunking}, e.g., Late Chunking). Resulting chunk embeddings are indexed and evaluated under two retrieval settings: (1) \textit {in-document retrieval} (needle-in-a-haystack) and (2) \textit {in-corpus retrieval} (multi-document). The pipeline supports multiple embedding and generative model families, enabling controlled comparison across chunking paradigms and model capacities}{figure.caption.2}{}}
